VERDICT: APPROVED_WITH_COMMENTS
The change set is largely acceptable, but one key part of the OrbitControls fluidity fix is currently ineffective and should be corrected.

Critical findings / analysis:
- Auth gate integration is correctly wired: `page.tsx` is now wrapped with `AuthGuard`, and unauthenticated users are redirected before rendering the Cortes workspace.
- Touch/controls tuning in `viewport-3d.tsx` is directionally good (touch mappings, panning mode, speed/damping tuning).
- However, `DampingInvalidator` is checking control fields (`sphericalDelta`, `panOffset`, `scale`) that are not exposed by the OrbitControls instance in this stack (three-stdlib/drei). As written, this movement check will evaluate false, so the self-sustaining invalidation loop does not run as intended under `frameloop="demand"`. That means post-drag damping can still stop abruptly.
- Large local/generated file churn appears in `.local/share/pnpm/store` and `.next` caches; those should not be part of task commits.

Security:
- No serious security violations observed in this diff.

Next actions:
1) Replace `DampingInvalidator` logic with a reliable signal (e.g., invalidate on controls start/change/end with a short decay loop, or use exposed APIs/state that actually exist on OrbitControls).
2) Re-test damping behavior specifically after pointer/touch release with `frameloop="demand"` to confirm smooth deceleration.
3) Exclude local cache/build artifacts from the commit (pnpm store, Next dev cache/logs) and keep only source changes.

